<br>
nadesico158, taking level 34 as an example, the level 34 earth and air pets can be bought in the local magician guild of most cities.  While the level 34 water and fire pets must be researched, you can buy the level 29 scrolls for these pets at your local magician guild also, so you don't have to chain research the level 16, 20, 24, and 29 scrolls for these pets.  At level 39 all but earth can be purchased in Katta Castellum in Luclin and at 44 all can be purchased in Katta Castellum.  At level 49 I believe that two must be researched and after that, well, that's not reallly on my radar screen but I frequently see higher level pet scrolls on sale at the bazaar.  The magician's spell list at Eq.castersrealm.com has more info on which pets are purchaseable and which need to be researched.<br>
<br>
<br>
If anyone notices any errors or omissions, please correct me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugaladwynxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GaladwynXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 11:44:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=718.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/pubimage.asp?id_=570233  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chain Research</span><hr size=1> I certainly hope he wouldn't put himself through all that I know I am not. For right now I am sticking to the ones I can buy at the vendors and go from there if I want a different pet.  Very nicely put I might add.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
